Privacy Policy for ChatGPT Pinner
Last updated: August 5, 2025

1. Introduction
ChatGPT Pinner is a Chrome extension that allows users to pin important ChatGPT messages for later reference. We value your privacy and are committed to protecting your data.

2. Information We Collect
We do NOT collect, store, or transmit any personal or sensitive user data.

The extension runs locally in your browser and does not send any information to external servers.

3. How We Use Information
All data (e.g., pinned messages) is stored locally on your device using Chrome‚Äôs storage API. This data is:

Only accessible to you.

Not shared with any third parties.

Not used for analytics or advertising.

4. Permissions Explanation
The extension uses the following permissions strictly for core functionality:

storage: Save pinned messages locally.

activeTab, scripting, tabs: Enable interaction with the active ChatGPT tab to identify and pin messages.

host_permissions: Limited to chat.openai.com and chatgpt.com only.

We do not use these permissions to track your activity.

5. Data Sharing and Third Parties
We do not share any data with third-party services or partners. Your usage of the extension is entirely private.

6. Security
Your pinned data is stored using Chrome‚Äôs secure local storage. Since no data is transmitted externally, the risk of unauthorized access is minimal.

7. Children‚Äôs Privacy
This extension does not target children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect any personal information from minors.

8. Changes to This Policy
We may update this privacy policy if the extension adds new features. All updates will be posted here with a revised ‚ÄúLast updated‚Äù date.

